ss names might cause problems, so I think we should keep a one-to-one structure in dedicated files and ensure to import NativeImageSupport.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gaZ4EBY0Dth89HThDFdcgVXe|fc_05db16ac799a99ce0169f882653a78819c8b36b2b79834f485", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport\" tests/src -g '*.scala' -g '*.java' | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1159, "output": 977, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38488, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777893971767, "responseId": "resp_05db16ac799a99ce0169f882545494819c813cd6b2b5d730e6"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_gaZ4EBY0Dth89HThDFdcgVXe|fc_05db16ac799a99ce0169f882653a78819c8b36b2b79834f485", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/1.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_wildfly_openssl/wildfly_openssl_java/SSLTest.java:import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\ntests/src/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/1.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_wildfly_openssl/wildfly_openssl_java/SSLTest.java:                if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\ntests/src/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/2.0.0.Alpha1/src/test/java/org_wildfly_openssl/wildfly_openssl_java/SSLTest.java:import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\ntests/src/org.wildfly.openssl/wildfly-openssl-java/2.0.0.Alpha1/src/test/java/org_wildfly_openssl/wildfly_openssl_java/SSLTest.java:                if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\ntests/src/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/4.4.2/src/test/java/org_eclipse_jdt_core_compiler/ecj/BatchAnnotationProcessorManagerTest.java:import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\ntests/src/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/4.4.2/src/test/java/org_ec