*\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I could implement a loop to make things more robust. I need to catch errors with NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e), but I wonder if the wrapper might not be recognized. The existing tests have a simple rethrow setup, but it seems I might not need to modify metadata. `git status` shows some untracked metadata that we didn't touch. I should ensure changes are properly noted, and there may be a need for a one-to-one mapping between the active and test classes. I’m contemplating whether to remove an original placeholder, but testing seems to involve runtime conditions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Configuring runtime arguments**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to configure `graalvmNative.binaries.test.runtimeArgs` with a huge classpath from `sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath`. The issue is that it includes the unbuilt macroSupport output. During configuration, if the output directory doesn’t exist, the path string seems fine. I wonder if I might need to add `buildArgs(\\\"-H:+AllowJRTFileSystem\\\")` for the native compiler, but since I’m catching unsupported features, maybe that's not necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a runtime-compilation based refinement for the active class coverage.\n\nKey changes:\n- Updated `CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeTest.scala` to invoke the Scala 3 compiler during the JUnit test, so `JsonCodecMaker.make(...)` macro expansion happens inside the test JVM rather than only during Gradle test-source compilation.\n- Added bounded Native Image handling for the runtime compiler path:\n  - catches `Error`\n  - verifies it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)`\n  - rethrows unexpected errors\n- Added precompiled support fixtures used by the runtime-compiled source:\n  - `MacroRuntimeNames.methodMapper` exercises runtime module lookup plus method-based field retrieval.\n  - `MacroRuntimeNames.publicFieldHolder.mapper` exercises runtime module lookup plus fallback public-field retrieval.\n- Updated `build.gradle` to:\n  - add a `macroSupport` source set,\n  - include the support output on the test runtime classpath,\n  - pass the resolved test classpath into JVM and Native Image test runs.\n\nThis should reach the remaining `CompileTimeEval$QuoteScope` call sites via the public macro API during test execution rather than compile-time-only expansion. I did not compile or run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05db16ac799a99ce0169f882da1e24819cb4e828c6c3fc62c9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1721, "output": 768, "cacheRead": 50176, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52665, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777894093559, "responseId": "resp_05db16ac799a99ce0169f882ce3e80819cb0c1155c28a8dbe8"}, "toolResults": []}
